messages.message:
Curious if we have any libraries / utils / recommendations to compare different versions (semvers) in marketplace? e.g. if I want to get the latest version of a marketplace model / package, for example.

I wanted to use `packaging.version.parse`  from `packaging` lib but i don’t think it’s available for python 3.7, maybe we already have this implemented somewhere? (Definitely don’t want to re-invent the wheel here)

cc @shiqi

for reference, @Eric Han wrote this great little util on the frontend for it: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/master/webserver/shared/src/js/webpacked/lib/src/SolutionBuilder/utils/index.ts#L7. You could do something like this and sort them and take the highest
how come packaging.version.prase is not available for python 3.7?

```Yang@Shiqis-MBP base-images % python3
Python 3.7.3 (default, Mar  2 2022, 13:50:01) 
[Clang 13.0.0 (clang-1300.0.29.30)] on darwin
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
>>> from packaging import version
>>> version.parse('3.5.0')
<Version('3.5.0')>
>>> ```
hmm wierd, let me check again

according to the one and only source of all truth of the universe (https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11887762/how-do-i-compare-version-numbers-in-python) :stack-overflow:
```packaging.version.parse is a third-party utility but is used by setuptools (so you probably already have it installed)```
DID YOU HEAR THAT YOU PROBABLY ALREADY HAVE IT INSTALLED
